title: PPPP’s Mehboob Ali Khan Bajarani Mahar wins PS-6 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Mehboob Ali Khan Bajarani has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-6 Kashmore-III by securing 86,365 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Abdul Qayyum of Jamiat Ulema-i-Islam Pakistan who bagged 9,945 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 55.26%.
